    {
      "type": "note",
      "id": "Q6x8vg",
      "x": 3600,
      "y": 1010,
      "name": "Why-composition note",
      "width": 360,
      "height": 0,
      "content": "‘Why this look’ = composite (Option A). The weather + occasion context is the templated chips above (backend data). This sentence is the AI's item-coordination reasoning, revived from the `reasoning` field the code currently discards — the model only knows the clothes (colour/fit/type), NOT weather/occasion/style. Future Option B: feed weather+occasion into the AI prompt for one richer single sentence — needs an AI-service + Go↔Python contract change + a quality spike."
    },
